  "prompt": "What companies provide healthcare business intelligence?",
  "response": "Many companies provide healthcare business intelligence solutions to help healthcare organizations manage and analyze their data effectively. Some notable companies in this space include:\n\n1. **IBM Watson Health**: Offers various healthcare analytics and AI-driven solutions to enhance clinical decision-making and operational efficiency.\n\n2. **Optum**: A subsidiary of UnitedHealth Group, provides health services and analytics emphasizing data-driven insights for better healthcare outcomes.\n\n3. **Cerner Corporation**: Specializes in healthcare technology, including EMR systems and data analytics to improve clinical and operational performance.\n\n4. **McKesson**: Provides pharmaceutical distribution and healthcare IT solutions, including data analytics for better patient care and operational workflow.\n\n5. **Philips Healthcare**: Offers health technology solutions, including data analytics, to support clinical decision-making and improve patient outcomes.\n\n6. **Epic Systems**: Known for its electronic health record (EHR) software, it also offers analytics tools to help healthcare organizations leverage their data.\n\n7. **Allscripts**: Provides healthcare IT solutions, including EHR and practice management systems, supplemented by data analytics capabilities.\n\n8. **GE Healthcare**: Offers a range of medical imaging and information technologies, including analytics platforms for healthcare data analysis.\n\n9. **SAS Health**: Provides advanced analytics and business intelligence solutions tailored specifically for the healthcare industry.\n\n10. **Oracle Health**: Dedicated healthcare solutions that include data management and analytics to optimize clinical and operational performance.\n\nThese organizations leverage advanced technologies such as AI, machine learning, and big data analytics to provide actionable insights that help improve patient care, streamline operations, and drive better financial performance in the healthcare industry.",
